 J. Sabato's Crystal Ball  |access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n|style=\"background:#f66\"|{{sort|104|Safe R}}\n|January 16, 2020\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Politico]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/2020-election/race-forecasts-and-predictions/governor/|title=We rated every gubernatorial race in 2020. Here's who we think will win.|website= Poltico|access-date= November 19, 2019}}</ref>\n|style=\"background:#fcc\"|{{sort|100|Lean R}}\n|November 19, 2019\n|}\n\n===Polling===\n\n\n{{collapse top|1=<span style=\"font-size:88%;\">Hypothetical polling</span>|left=yes|bg=#B0CEFF;line-height:135%;|border=none}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size{{efn|name=key}}\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Jim<br>Justice (R)\n! style=\"width:100px;\"| Joe<br>Manchin (D)\n! Undecided\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [http://wvmetronews.com/2019/08/30/west-virginia-poll-if-manchin-gets-in-right-now-he-would-beat-justice/ Research America Inc.]\n| August 14\u201322, 2019\n| 501\n| \u00b1&nbsp;4.4%\n| 39%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}| '''49%'''\n| 12%\n|}\n{{collapse bottom}}\n\n===Results===\n{{Election box begin \n| title = West Virginia gubernatorial election, 2020\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n| candidate = TBA\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link \n| candidate = TBA\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link \n| candidate = Quintin Gerard Caldwell\n| party = Independent (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage =\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link \n| candidate = Erika Kolenich \n| party = Libertarian Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link \n| candidate = David Sartin\n| party = Independent (United States)\n| v